                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>California <hi rend=\"underline\">San Fran</hi></placeName>\n                <date>May 29 1862</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>Reply to “Wrong doings in <placeName>California</placeName></p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Editor of the Occident</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Revd. Sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">My attention has<lb/> been drawn to the above article in the<lb/>\n                gleaner of the <date>23d</date> Inst. copied from<lb/> the Occident of <date>April\n                    62</date>—in which it<lb/> states “Two <persName>C<hi rend=\"underline\"\n                        >ohamin</hi></persName> applied to<lb/> congregation “Sherith Israel” to be\n                mar-<lb/>-ried by <persName>Dr. Henry</persName> to widows, and<lb/> he refused.”\n                    <persName>Theophilis</persName> (upon whom<lb/> I suspect I could lay my\n                finger)<lb/> does <hi rend=\"underline\">not</hi> tell the Truth. <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >I</hi> am the<lb/> wife of one of the “<persName>Cohanim</persName>”\n                alluded<lb/> to, and beg to state the facts to<lb/> you.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I arrived in <placeName>California</placeName> in <date>1850</date>,\n                and<lb/> in the spring of <date>1852</date> left with my<lb/> first husband on a\n                trading voyage<lb/> to the <placeName>South Pacific Islands</placeName>, and</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p35q4s610/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
