                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(center)\">2</p>\n            <p>unfortunately lost him at one of the<lb/> Tonga<add>?</add> group in <date>September\n                    1852</date>l, I returned<lb/> to this city <date>Dec. 27<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                    >th</hi></date> of the same year<lb/> dreadfully distressed in mind—in<lb/> fact\n                inconsolable. My Father (god rest<lb/> his dear soul) was here till <date>July\n                    1854</date><lb/> during that period he made the ac-<lb/>-quaintance of\n                    <persName>Mr. P.</persName> and wished me<lb/> very much to marry him. I\n                told<lb/> him no—but so anxious was<lb/> he, that, previous to his departure for<lb/>\n                <placeName>New York</placeName> he left word with a friend<lb/> to occasionally urge\n                the matter to me.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">In <date>1858</date> I was engaged to<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr. P.</persName> but called his attention to Chap. 21<lb/> V. 14 of\n                Leviticus: he said he would con-<lb/>-sult a <hi rend=\"underline\">Lamdan</hi>, which\n                he did, and<lb/> this gentleman said, <hi rend=\"underline\">that</hi> passage<lb/>\n                referred to the <hi rend=\"underline\">High Priest</hi>! I was<lb/> satisfied and our\n                engagement<lb/> went on, to the knowledge more or<lb/> less of nearly all the Jews\n                in the</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p35q4s610/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
