                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(center)\">3</p>\n            <p>city, for <persName>Mr. P.</persName> and myself regularly attended<lb/> synagogue\n                during that period we<lb/> visited at <persName>Dr. Henry's</persName> certainly <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">once</hi> a<lb/> week (many times more frequently) and he, and\n                the<lb/> late <persName>Mrs. Henry</persName> used repeatedly ask what<lb/> we\n                visited for? On the <date>15<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> of Feb.<lb/> 1859</date>\n                <persName>Mr. P.</persName> applied to the Board of the<lb/> Congregation “Sherith\n                Israel” for permission<lb/> to marry—which was granted and,<lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\"><persName>Dr. Henry</persName> had written and fitted out</hi><lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">our Casubba</hi> a thing he subsequently<lb/> told us he very\n                seldom did before the<lb/> day it was wanted. So much for <persName>Dr<lb/>\n                    Henry's</persName> refusal!</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">On the <date>24<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> of Feb.</date> the day\n                previous<lb/> to the one appointed for our marriage<lb/>\n                <persName>Dr. Henry</persName> called at ½ 7 A. M. and after<lb/> some slight\n                circumlocution asked me<lb/> if my former Husband had Brothers?<lb/>\n                <sic>at</sic> first I could not recollect, I felt<lb/> confused and without knowing\n                why<lb/> felt certain <persName>Dr. H</persName> had not come on<lb/> a friendly\n                errand. I said I believed<lb/> there were two but I was not sure</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p35q4s610/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
